    <completion-notes>
      Seed deployed to Spaarke Dev. Row id 4fe49430-aa62-f111-ab0c-70a8a58ae145.
      Script: scripts/Seed-AiPersonaDefault.ps1 (cloned from Seed-KnowledgeScopes.ps1
      canonical pattern; idempotent — re-run returns `unchanged`).

      Canonical-text discovery: `BuildDefaultSystemPrompt()` is defined in
      `PlaybookChatContextProvider.cs` (not `SprkChatAgentFactory.cs` as the POML
      goal said — minor drift in the POML). The factory delegates to the context
      provider which invokes the method. Captured the standalone-mode branch
      (lines 541-569; playbookName == null), which is the FR-04 SYS-default
      fallback. The named-playbook branch (lines 526-536) is a runtime-dynamic
      template (string interpolation on playbookName) and is NOT the SYS-default;
      it will continue to be produced by the playbook-attached resolution path.

      Verbatim match: stored sprk_systemprompt is byte-identical to the C# 11
      raw-string-normalized canonical text (2042 chars, LF). Verified via
      independent Python diff against source — `c:\tmp\verify-persona-text.py`.

      Row shape decisions:
        - sprk_name           = "SYS-DEFAULT"   (per POML goal)
        - sprk_personacode    = "SYS-DEF"       (10-char schema limit; the
                                                 invocation argument suggested
                                                 "SYS-DEFAULT-PERSONA@v1" which
                                                 exceeds the limit deployed in
                                                 task 001 — used short form)
        - sprk_scopetype      = 100000000 (Global)   per Q1
        - sprk_availableadhoc = true                 (resolver fallback)
        - sprk_parentpersonaid = null                (root of inheritance chain)
        - sprk_tags           = "system,default,fallback,chat"

      BFF publish-size delta: 0 MB (no BFF code changed).
      Verbatim reference: notes/task-004-system-prompt-source.txt
      Evidence:           notes/task-004-completion.md
