  <prompt>
    Seed the default global SYS- persona row in the `sprk_aipersona` entity (created in
    task 001). The row's `systemPrompt` field MUST contain the current hardcoded
    `BuildDefaultSystemPrompt()` text VERBATIM from `SprkChatAgentFactory.cs`. This is the
    fallback row returned by `IScopeResolverService.ResolvePersonaForChatAsync` (task 003)
    when no tenant CUST- or playbook-attached override exists.

    Critical-path context: FR-04 binding — behavior with no tenant/playbook override MUST
    be identical to today. The whole point of the seed is to make the data-driven cutover
    in task 005 behavior-preserving. Any drift between the seeded text and the original
    `BuildDefaultSystemPrompt()` output would change the chat-agent voice on the cutover
    PR — a regression the project explicitly forbids.

    Seed mechanism options: (a) data-only solution row imported via `pac solution import`;
    (b) PowerShell deploy script using Dataverse Web API; (c) idempotent migration script
    run at deploy time. Pick whichever matches the existing scope-seed pattern. Reuse
    existing seed conventions; do not invent a new mechanism. The seed MUST be idempotent
    (re-run is no-op if row exists).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior Dataverse engineer experienced with Spaarke scope-library seed patterns and the
    `dataverse-deploy` skill.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A single `sprk_aipersona` row named "SYS-DEFAULT" exists in Spaarke Dev with
    `sprk_systemprompt` containing the verbatim text from
    `SprkChatAgentFactory.BuildDefaultSystemPrompt()` as of master at task-execution time.
    Seed script committed to repo, idempotent on re-run. Verification: querying via Web API
    returns the row with identical text. Acceptance criteria all green.
  </goal>

